# Day 21 - Longest Arithmetic Subsequence (Dynamic Programming)

## Problem

**LeetCode 1027 - Longest Arithmetic Subsequence**

Given an integer array `nums`, return the length of the longest arithmetic subsequence in `nums`.

An arithmetic subsequence is a sequence where the difference between every two consecutive elements is the same.

---

## Approaches Covered

1. Recursion
2. Memoization
3. Dynamic Programming (Optimal)

---

## Algorithm

For every pair of indices:

- Compute the common difference.
- Find the longest arithmetic subsequence ending at the previous index.
- Extend that subsequence by including the current element.

The optimal DP stores:

dp[i][diff] = Length of arithmetic subsequence ending at index i with common difference diff.

---

## Complexity

| Approach | Time | Space |
|----------|------|-------|
| Recursion | O(2ⁿ) | O(n) |
| Memoization | O(n²) | O(n²) |
| DP (HashMap) | O(n²) | O(n²) |

